The ATEX workplace directive 1999/92/EC (also known as ATEX 137) places obligations on employers to protect workers from explosive-atmosphere hazards. Article 4 and Annex I explicitly require the employer to draw up and maintain a single, comprehensive document—the Explosion Protection Document (EPD)—that demonstrates compliance.
