Bellows-seal bonnets are used in place of conventional packing when zero (or near-zero) leakage to atmosphere is mandatory. Typical triggers include:
- toxic, radioactive, or highly hazardous fluids (e.g., chlorine, phosgene, hydrogen sulfide);
- strict fugitive-emission limits (EPA, TA-Luft, ISO 15848, etc.) on volatile organic compounds (VOCs);
- high-vacuum service where in-leakage of air or moisture cannot be tolerated;
- extremely valuable or pure process fluids where any loss is unacceptable.
